shaving my legs. My mother hates the fuzz and I’m not a fan of the pain either. I’ve tried waxing and depilatory creams but neither was too effective. Any suggestions?

Yasmine (Monaco)

There aren’t many of the convenient depilatory creams on the market that are not also extremely drying to the fragile skin of the legs. They’re also not great at regrowth. You should try one of the more luxurious after-shave products particularly designed for Asian skins. It will slow down the process of regrowth and leave behind no stubble or rash. Try The Body Shop or any of the products at Victoria’s Secret. Make sure your razor is always new and that your dry shave skin product is always applied as soon after you get it. A body scrub, waxing at the beginning of summer after you’ve been on the beach for a few early dips or just pluck it for the best results in a salon.
